overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by integrating a database for response storage, an admin dashboard
  for data access, and an authentication system. The initial codebase was
  evaluated against the Statement of Work, revealing the need for a database
  schema, API endpoints for data handling, and an admin interface. Key decisions
  included using NeonDB for PostgreSQL, updating demographic fields to align
  with SOW requirements, and implementing a simple password-based
  authentication. Initially, a custom session management system was developed,
  but it was later streamlined by leveraging Next.js middleware for more
  efficient and cleaner route protection. The implementation covered updating
  data models, creating RESTful APIs for questionnaire submission and retrieval
  (including CSV export), and building a functional admin login and dashboard.
  The entire system was thoroughly tested in the browser to confirm that
  questionnaire submissions were saved, admin access was secure, and data export
  worked correctly.
